name: unary_qf4pfd
jaxpr:
{ lambda ; a:f32[4]. let
    b:f32[4] = neg a
    c:f32[4] = exp b
    d:f32[4] = add 1.0:f32[] c
    e:f32[4] = div 1.0:f32[] d
    f:f32[4] = exp e
    g:f32[4] = integer_pow[y=2] f
  in (g,) }
hlo:
module @jit_unary_qf4pfd attributes {mhlo.num_partitions = 1 : i32, mhlo.num_replicas = 1 : i32} {
  func.func public @main(%arg0: tensor<4xf32>) -> (tensor<4xf32> {jax.result_info = "result"}) {
    %0 = stablehlo.negate %arg0 : tensor<4xf32>
    %1 = stablehlo.exponential %0 : tensor<4xf32>
    %cst = stablehlo.constant dense<1.000000e+00> : tensor<f32>
    %2 = stablehlo.broadcast_in_dim %cst, dims = [] : (tensor<f32>) -> tensor<4xf32>
    %3 = stablehlo.add %2, %1 : tensor<4xf32>
    %cst_0 = stablehlo.constant dense<1.000000e+00> : tensor<f32>
    %4 = stablehlo.broadcast_in_dim %cst_0, dims = [] : (tensor<f32>) -> tensor<4xf32>
    %5 = stablehlo.divide %4, %3 : tensor<4xf32>
    %6 = stablehlo.exponential %5 : tensor<4xf32>
    %7 = stablehlo.multiply %6, %6 : tensor<4xf32>
    return %7 : tensor<4xf32>
  }
}
